From the equation, we identify
\[a^2 = 18 \quad \text{and} \quad b^2 = 2\]
Next, we find the coordinates of the foci using
\[c = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2}\]
We calculate \(a + b\) and find the distance between the foci from there.
\[
\begin{align*}
a &= \sqrt{18} \quad \text{and} \\
b &= \sqrt{2}
\end{align*}
\]
\[
\begin{align*}
c &= \sqrt{18 + 2} \\
c &= \sqrt{20} \\
c &= 2\sqrt{5}
\end{align*}
\]
The distance between the foci is \(2c\):
\[
\begin{align*}
2c &= 2 \times 2\sqrt{5} \\
2c &= 4\sqrt{5}
\end{align*}
\]
Thus, the distance between the foci is: \boxed{4\sqrt{5}}
\end{answer}

